@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Zarro' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Game play is simple: just click on one of the 4 arrows that are
located somewhere on the game board. Depending on where it is
pointing, that arrow will move by one space in that direction and
all tiles that are on the same row or column will also move by one
space. A tile (or arrow) that is located on one edge will move to
the opposing edge of the board. Note that as the game can be played
by using the cursor moving keys of the keyboard, you can move the
arrows with the corresponding cursor keys...

  When at least 4 tiles of the same pattern are in line, either
horizontally or vertically. These tiles are then removed and you
get points according to their number; 4 tiles give 1 point, 5 tiles
give 5 points, 6 tiles give 25 points and 7 tiles give 125 points.
That score increases by 10 multiplied by the number of game boards
completed... if, you make series of 5 or more tiles of the same
pattern...

  One thing to watch for is that you should avoid leaving less than
4 tiles of one type on the board... as the game would be over when
it is no longer possible to make series of at least 4 tiles of the
same pattern.

  Continue to remove tiles until only the arrows remain, then,
Zarro will generate a new game board, and the game will continue...

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

